data.graph

Class Vertex

  • java.lang.Object
    • data.graph.Vertex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KeySortable

    public class Vertex
extends java.lang.Object
implements KeySortable
    A vertex in a graph when the ASCII labyrinth is turned into a graph, its tiles are put into vertices. A vertex can have at most 8 edges linking to other tiles as there are at most 8 adjacent tiles to a single tile in the labyrinth.

    • Method Detail

      • addLink

        public void addLink(Edge e)
        Adds an edge to the links array. The edge contains a reference to this vertex and another that is adjacent to the labyrinth tile. It also has a weight variable to determine 'distances' between vertices, although it only increases if either vertex is a wall tile.
        Parameters:
        e - an edge to add to the links array
